&lt;p&gt;VFX was only half the project, there were also storybook animations for certain narrative portions of the film. I was provided with Photoshop assets from an illustrator who drew them. My job was to take the layers/characters and animate them. I decided to go beyond the 2D realm of a book and try a sort of 3D parallaxing style. The clients enjoyed it so I went through with it.&lt;/p&gt;

