&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I also was hired to make the show&amp;rsquo;s intro sequence. This was accomplished with an XBox Kinect hooked up to a DSLR with synchronized recording. I was then able to import the footage to a program that let me manipulate the 3D data in space and make my own camera moves. After this I exported the new rendered footage into Adobe After Effects to add more 3D elements like layers of code and particles, along with some sweet processing like motion blur and glows.&lt;/p&gt;

